Docs:
    -- HTML
     - We have different built-in blocks to structure our page
     • <header> → Used for introductory content of page such as:
                   - <nav>
                     - <ul> <li> <a>
                   - Can also be inside of an <article> or of a <section>
     • <main> → Represent the main content of the page → Only 1 main per page, otherwise VALIDATION ERROR!
                  <section>       → Group related content   
                    <h2,h3,>      → This is compolsury, a heading inside each section!
                    <article>
                      <section>  
                      <section>
                    <article>
                    <article>
                    ...
                  <section>
                    <heading>
                    <article>
                    <article>
                    <article>
                    ...
     • <aside> → Used for advertisment or content not related to our <main> content
     • <footer> → Use for conclusion content of page such as:
                 - <nav>
                   - <ul> <li> <a>
     
                 - Can be also Inside of an <article> or of a <section>